OL,3,CConservative leader 'understands'
OL,4,Cpublic opposition to elected mayors
OL,6,FPublic opposition to the introduction
OL,7,Fof new elected mayors in the South of
OL,8,FEngland is "understandable", according
OL,9,Fto the Conservative leader.
OL,11,FKemi Badenoch said "devolution doesn't
OL,12,Ffix problems" but as Labour was
OL,13,Fpushing ahead with the reforms "we
OL,14,Fhave to make the best of it".
OL,16,FThe government is creating new mayoral
OL,17,Fpositions for 'Sussex and Brighton'
OL,18,Fand 'Hampshire and the Solent'.
