OL,4,Cpublic opposition to elected mayors
OL,6,FThey would be similar to those in
OL,7,FLondon and Greater Manchester ` with
OL,8,Fpowers over transport, housing,
OL,9,Femployment, policing and fire services.
OL,11,FThe role does not replace local
OL,12,Fcouncils, but ministers are separately
OL,13,Fcarrying out a major shake-up of local
OL,14,Fgovernment, abolishing separate
OL,15,Fdistrict and county councils and
OL,16,Fforming new large unitary authorities.
